  "body": "### Description\n- When running on PKI-enabled mode, when validating the block header, the node must check if the CMS message is present in the extraData field (reject empty CMS messages).\n- The node should not validate the CMS content as part of the header validation, it should just check if it exists.\n\nWe can use the factory `QbftBlockHeaderValidationRulesetFactory` to conditionally add the rule when PKI is enabled.",
